    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/135005701/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """UNIT 1
FORMAL ENGLISH: ACADEMIC COMMUNICATION

1.1.Formal vs. informal language: Definition, characteristics and functions.

1.2.Building academic vocabulary: dictionaries and word-database.

1.3.E-mail writing in formal settings.

1.4.General and technical meanings.

UNIT 2
ACTIVE READING IN ACADEMIC ENGLISH
2.1 Identifying types of texts.

2.2 Reading for the main idea and the detail.

2.3.Organizing and summarizing key information.

2.4.Predicting information from visual aids.

2.5.Annotating texts.

UNIT 3
ACTIVE LISTENING IN ACADEMIC ENGLISH
3.1. Predicting lecture content.

3.2. Identifying main and secondary ideas.

3.3. Note-taking.

3.4. Organizing notes.

UNIT 4
WRITTEN COMMUNICATION IN ACADEMIC CONTEXTS
4.1.The Writing process: from the outline to the draft.: audience, purpose, style, tone.

4.2.Elements of the text organization: the sentence and the paragraph. Sentence problems.

4.3.Structuring the paragraph: intraparagraph and interparagraph cohesion. Transition signals.

4.4.Defining, classifying and describing. Describing a process. Describing graphics.

4.5.Expressing causality and result. Problem-solution.

4.6. Comparing and contrasting.

4.7. Writing summaries and essays

4.8.The technical/scientific report: structure and content.The Abstract: purpose, types and structure. Referencing and citation. Plagiarism.

UNIT 5
ORAL COMMUNICATION
5.1 Characteristics of oral communication

5.2 Speaking in meetings

5.3. Oral presentations:
5.3.1 Preparation and planning
5.3.2. Non-verbal communication
5.3.3. Voice and pronunciation
5.3.4. Relationship with the audience: creating interest
5.3.5. Structure of the presentation. Transition signals
5.3.6. Introducing visuals

UNIT 6
PROFESSIONAL ENGLISH
6.1 The Cover letter. The letter of motivation

6.2. The Curriculum Vitae/ The Resumé. Personal statements.

6.3. The Job interview"""@es ;
